description: The BCCI is planning a meeting with selectors and team management to discuss Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli's future, focusing on the 2027 ODI World Cup. Clarity on their roles and performance expectations will be provided, with advice to play more domestic cricket to maintain match fitness and form.
title: IND vs SA: BCCI set to hold crucial meeting on Rohit and Kohli’s ODI future

author: LAKSHIMA SAREEN
description: Assistant Professor Suman Chauhan was arrested by the CBI for her alleged role in the UKSSSC graduate-level recruitment exam paper leak. Chauhan is accused of solving questions and transmitting answers to a candidate, marking a significant development in uncovering the broader network behind the incident. The leak, which led to the exam's cancellation, has intensified calls for stricter examination safeguards.
title: CBI arrests Assistant Professor in UKSSSC paper leak case: Here is what happened so far

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Following Dharmendra's passing, a prayer meet saw industry heavyweights like Shah Rukh Khan and Salman Khan pay their respects.  His daughters, Esha and Ahana, have spoken about his ability to manage both his families with grace.  Hema Malini, in a past interview, emphasized her need for his love over material possessions, highlighting his consistent support.
title: Esha Deol on bond with father Dharmendra: ‘He beautifully managed both families, was a large-hearted man’

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Residents' prior warnings about flammable materials used in renovations at Wang Fuk Court were ignored, contributing to a devastating fire that claimed at least 128 lives. The blaze rapidly spread due to the materials and malfunctioning fire alarms, leading to arrests for manslaughter and corruption as Hong Kong mourns and calls for stronger safety oversight.
title: Hong Kong fire tragedy: Were authorities alerted long before? Key details

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
title: Karnataka power tussle: Breakthrough? Siddaramaiah, DKS meet over breakfast as CM battle heats up

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce celebrated an early Thanksgiving dinner at his new steakhouse with family and fans.  Swift even coined a fun nickname for the group. While unable to spend the actual holiday together due to Kelce's game and Swift's security concerns, the pre-holiday meal offered a glimpse into their festive traditions.
title: Taylor Swift & Travis Kelce’s steakhouse photo with Chiefs fans goes viral

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Eating certain foods like raw vegetables, tomatoes, citrus fruits, and coffee on an empty stomach can worsen gas, acidity, and bloating. Nutritionist Shweta Shah recommends gentler ways to enjoy these, such as cooking vegetables, combining tomatoes with other foods, having citrus mid-morning, and eating a snack before coffee. Simple morning swaps can significantly improve digestion.
title: Avoid these 4 foods on empty stomach to reduce gas & bloating

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: A hypothetical trade sending Kyle Schwarber to the Toronto Blue Jays for Davis Schneider and a pitching prospect is gaining traction. This move would inject much-needed middle-order power into Toronto's lineup, while Philadelphia could gain financial flexibility and younger talent. The deal offers significant offensive upgrades for Toronto and potential long-term roster balance for the Phillies.
title: MLB trade rumors: Blue Jays eye $79M Phillies star to strengthen middle order

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: India has launched Operation Sagar Bandhu to aid Sri Lanka following Cyclone Ditwah, which has claimed at least 80 lives. An Indian Air Force C-130J aircraft delivered approximately 12 tons of humanitarian aid, including tents, blankets, and food, to Colombo. This assistance underscores India's commitment to its 'Neighbourhood First' policy and Vision MAHASAGAR amidst the island nation's severe disaster.
title: ‘Operation Sagar Bandhu’: India flies 12 tonnes of aid to flood-hit Sri Lanka; island battered by Cyclone Ditwah

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Airbus has mandated a software upgrade for its A320 family aircraft, impacting over 6,000 planes globally. In India, IndiGo and Air India will ground over 350 planes for two to three days, potentially causing significant flight disruptions. This large-scale recall, one of Airbus's biggest, follows an incident that prompted a software review.
title: Over 350 planes hit: Airbus A320 software snag set to cause major flight disruptions — 10 things to know

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravichandran Ashwin highlights Gautam Gambhir's significant impact on India's white-ball cricket, crediting him for fostering a bolder, more proactive T20 approach. Gambhir's coaching, fueled by IPL talent like Abhishek Sharma, has led to recent successes and a redefined team identity, contrasting with Test struggles.
title: 'This is the real GG': R Ashwin reveals the side of Gautam Gambhir critics are ignoring

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: An Enforcement Directorate probe into illegal betting has uncovered a bike-taxi driver in Delhi whose bank account received over Rs 331 crore in eight months. Investigators suspect the account was used as a 'mule' for money laundering, with funds channeled to a luxury wedding linked to a Gujarat politician. The ED is tracing the entire transaction chain.
title: Used as 'mule': ED finds Rs 331cr in bike rider's account; money trail leads to viral Udaipur wedding

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: A computer applications graduate, Bandhu Maan Singh Sekhon, traded a promising career for organized crime in Canada. Initially working at a pharmacy, he soon entered the underworld, allegedly involved in extortion and weapon trafficking under the guidance of gangster Harry Chatha.  His criminal activities, including links to terror groups, led to his arrest in Canada.
title: Kaps cafe shooting: From car dealer dream to befriending terrorist; how Sekhon entered crime world

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: National Investigation Agency (NIA) discovered Rs 18 lakh cash in a hostel room at Al-Falah University, linked to Dr. Shaheen Shahid, arrested for the Delhi blast. The money is suspected to fund a 'white-coat terror module' operating from the university. Investigations are underway to trace the funds and identify associates involved in expanding the terror network.
title: 'White collar' terror module: NIA seizes Rs 18 lakh from Dr Shaheen’s room; probe intensifies

author: KUSHAGRA DIXIT
description: Delhi's groundwater faces alarming uranium contamination, ranking third nationally with 13-15% of samples exceeding safe limits. This rise from previous years raises public health concerns, especially with co-occurring high nitrate, fluoride, and salinity levels. Environmental groups are demanding greater transparency on water quality data and treatment protocols.
title: High uranium in Delhi groundwater: 15% samples exceed safe limits

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: The cocktail of alcohol and routine medications can create a recipe for disaster—compromising reflexes, burdening the liver, and triggering extreme reactions. Whether it's anti-anxiety meds, sleep enhancers, allergy medicines, or pain relief like paracetamol, the interactions can be harmful. Plus, heart, diabetes, and circulation drugs might also react unpredictably.
title: Liver specialist explains the medicines that should never be mixed with alcohol

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The US has halted visa processing for all Afghan passport holders, citing national security concerns following a shooting incident near the White House. The suspect, an Afghan national who arrived in 2021, critically injured two National Guard members. This move underscores the administration's commitment to protecting Americans amidst ongoing security reviews.
title: 'Priority to ...': US pauses visas for all traveling on Afghan passports; move after WH shooting

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma are set to return for the opening ODI against South Africa in Ranchi, sparking immense fan excitement. Their intense practice sessions, including a viral clip of Rohit's playful wink at Kohli, highlight their camaraderie and competitive spirit. This series is crucial for India to bounce back after their Test series loss.
title: Ro-Ko storm loading? Rohit Sharma smashes six, winks at Virat Kohli in Ranchi - See viral pics

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli is set to return for India's ODI series against South Africa, aiming to build on his recent form. He boasts an impressive record against South Africa and at Ranchi specifically. Kohli is also on the verge of a significant international milestone, needing just 337 runs to reach 28,000.
title: South Africa's nightmare? Virat Kohli's record says it all ahead of Ranchi ODI

author: TNN
description: A Pune IT consultant was stabbed in the rib after a minor collision between his scooter and an SUV in Kharadi. The SUV driver and a female companion allegedly assaulted the victim following an argument. Police are searching for the duo, with the driver identified and expected to be apprehended soon. The incident occurred Wednesday evening.
title: Pune horror: IT firm consultant stabbed during road tiff; cops look for SUV driver, woman

author: SHARIQ MAJEED
description: A permanent resident in Canada, Mandeep Kaur Grewal, initially reported to have died in a car accident, was allegedly murdered by her brother-in-law. Gurjot Singh Khaira has been charged with second-degree murder and indignity to human remains. The family remains in shock, unaware of the motive behind the alleged killing.
title: Grief turns to shock: Indian-origin bride's Canada 'accident' now murder

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Neuroscience reveals that consistent habits can reshape the brain, enhancing thinking, learning, and stress resilience. AIIMS-trained Neurosurgeon Dr. Arun L Naik shares 10 key habits, from consistent sleep to daily learning, that stimulate neural circuits and foster a smarter brain. Practicing these daily leads to sharper recall and peak performance.
title: Neurosurgeon with 25 years of experience shares 10 habits that make the brain smarter

author: TNN
description: A Lucknow bike mechanic staged his own kidnapping to escape his pregnant wife, paying a minor to deliver a false abduction story. Police uncovered the deception through CCTV footage and surveillance, revealing the man's motive was to 'get rid of her' after frequent arguments.
title: DIY abduction fail: Man stages own kidnapping to get ‘rid’ of his pregnant wife; police unravel plot

author: TNN
description: India's economy surged by 8.2% in the July-September quarter, driven by a strong manufacturing rebound and robust services activity. This marks the fastest expansion in six quarters, with domestic demand fueling production ahead of the festival season. Economists now anticipate full-year growth to exceed 7%, bolstered by pro-growth policies and reforms.
title: GDP grew 8.2% in Q2, fastest in 6 quarters

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Dhanush and Kriti Sanon's 'Tere Ishk Mein' has stormed the box office, exceeding expectations with a massive Rs 16.5 crore opening day. This romantic drama's success, fueled by positive reviews and word-of-mouth, marks the highest opener of Dhanush's Bollywood career and signals a strong comeback for intense romantic films. The film's performance is already outshining other releases.
title: Tere Ishk Mein' box office collection day 1: Dhanush, Kriti starrer mints Rs 16 crore

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Utah Mammoth captain Clayton Keller, despite the sudden passing of his father, Bryan, chose to play the very next day against the Dallas Stars. This decision highlights his profound loyalty and inner strength, honoring his father while supporting his team. Coach Andre Tourigny emphasized the organization's unwavering support for Keller, underscoring their family-first approach.
title: Utah Mammoth captain Clayton Keller honors late father

author: TNN
description: A man in Uttar Pradesh, India, was found trapped inside a leopard cage after reportedly entering it while intoxicated. The incident occurred in Bahraich district, where a leopard had recently killed a villager. Forest officials and police conducted a two-hour rescue operation to free the man, who was later released with a warning. Efforts to capture the leopard continue.
title: UP: ‘Drunk’ man found stuck inside leopard trap cage in Bahraich
